      <hedline>
        <hl1>Putting Teachers First</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from James H Norton 3d on Aug 10 article on software programs intended to replace college and university teachers</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Why would Northwestern University pay Dr. Roger C. Schank to create educational software programs intended to replace college and university teachers (''No Lectures or Teachers, Just Software'' Aug. 10).  As a professor of literature and humanities at Marian College in Indianapolis, I find Dr. Schank's project morally unconscionable in its disregard for the special learning needs of each individual student. Tuition-paying parents deserve to have their children guided by human sensitivity, not by technology.</p>
        <p>JAMES H. NORTON III, PH.D.  Indianapolis</p>
      </block>
